From: Werner <werner@armbian.com>
Date: Thu Jul 17 14:30:00 2026 +0000
Subject: bluetooth: hci: ignore -22 for WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY on Marlin/uwe5622

The Marlin (uwe5622) Bluetooth controller reports HCI_OP_WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY
as supported but rejects it with -22 (EINVAL) during initialization, causing
the entire HCI setup to fail and the controller to remain unusable.

Work around this firmware quirk by ignoring -22 errors specifically for
WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY (0x080f), allowing initialization to continue.

Signed-off-by: Werner <werner@armbian.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c b/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
index df23245d6ccd..fc9060e21fc0 100644
--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
@@ -268,10 +268,17 @@ int __hci_cmd_sync_status_sk(struct hci_dev *hdev, u16 opcode, u32 plen,
 
 	if (IS_ERR(skb)) {
 		if (!event)
 			bt_dev_err(hdev, "Opcode 0x%4.4x failed: %ld", opcode,
 				   PTR_ERR(skb));
+
+		/* Ignore -22 for WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY - some controllers
+		 * report it as supported but reject it (e.g., Marlin/uwe5622)
+		 */
+		if (PTR_ERR(skb) == -EINVAL && opcode == 0x080f)
+			return 0;
+
 		return PTR_ERR(skb);
 	}
 
 	status = skb->data[0];
 
-- 